blem solving and prioritization in a fast-paced environment. Due to the highly collaborative nature of this position, strong interpersonal skills and cross-functional team experience is important. Who we\u2019re looking for: Responsibilities: Experienced creative leader and manager of a team of designers Design digital content, pages and experiences Design and develop social content in conjunction with the Marketing and Communications team Create motion studies and animations for prototyping and production Adopt Auth0 design systems and standards, scaling them across Auth0 web properties Lead/Co-Lead projects from conception, design, to execution and advocacy. Design and maintain style guides, toolkits and other design documents Elevate the Auth0 brand through compelling, story-driven experience across devices Collaborate with our internal Marketing Engineering team to translate our brand identity UI into successful content for our customers Speak and present to stakeholders and agency partners on design strategy. Work with senior team members to establish priority, fidelity and delivery of tasks. Lead teams in conceptualizing the design for digital experiences Define the visual digital design system and establish best practices for UI Partner with Project Managers and other Designers to create efficient workflows and processes Motivate and inspire our team by being a thought leader and sharing best practices with designers Strong understanding of site architecture, user experience, visual interfaces and device functionality Knows how to create UIs that follow design system standards and maximize consistency, while also pushing the brand and design system forward Ability to present quality conceptual prototypes Create, design, and develop digital assets to support interactive campaigns including email blasts, landing pages, advertising, and other digital projects Develop concepts, graphics, and layouts for Auth0\u2019s website and microsites Design templates for emails, landing pages, and other communications within our marketing automation platform Design business templates for company use (i.e., PowerPoint, business cards). Design for trade show displays, banners, PDF reports, eBooks, and case studies Work with team members, brief and advise them with regard to proposal style, format, production, and timelines Extend brand continuity in visual messaging across all channels Responsible for the growth and maintenance of a high functioning team Partner with the marketing team in strategic planning Requirements: Minimum of 2 years of creative management experience at an agency or in-house. Degree or similar qualification in graphic design, fine arts or advertising with a digital focus. Demonstrated skills for collaborating closely with other cross-functional marketing partners, designers, and engineers. Outstanding mentor and listener. Effectively help the team to build on strengths, prioritize and navigate challenges. Experience designing for mobile, responsive design, and animation. Understanding of growth channels, targeting and iterative creative testing. Solid understanding of performance design, as well as composition, color, imagery, and photography. Experience designing and implementing A/B and multivariate tests. Experience in optimizing and developing content. Experience designing digital templates for email and landing pages within a marketing automation tool or similar platforms a plus and extra bonus if you\u2019ve designed for BranfolderKnowledge of design techniques, interactive tools, and principles. Experience with media production, communication design, and a strong eye for typography and color. Excellent understanding of web and mobile standards, including responsive design and usability. Clear, compelling presentation and communication style. Preferred Locations: #US; Auth0\u2019s mission is to help developers innovate faster. Every company is becoming a software company and developers are at the center of this shift. They need better tools and building blocks so they can stay focused on innovating. One of these building blocks is identity: authentication and authorization. That\u2019s what we do. Our platform handles 2.5B logins per month for thousands of customers around the world. From indie makers to Fortune 500 companies, we can handle any use case. We like to think that we are helping make the internet safer. We have raised $210M to date and are growing quickly. Our team is spread across more than 35 countries and we are proud to continually be recognized as a great place to work. Culture is critical to us, and we are transparent about our vision and principles. Join us on this journey to make developers more productive while making the internet safer! More Jobs Website Twitter Or view all jobs: Developer jobs Marketing jobs Product jobs Design jobs Sales jobs Support jobs & learn about: remote work Related Jobs Senior Product Designer TaxJar TaxJar makes sales tax filing easier for online sellers and merchants. See local jurisdictional tax reports, get payment reminders, and more! Anywhere Full Time Posted 1 week ago Senior UX Designer & Researcher (Remote) Respondent High-quality research participants you need, for any research study Anywhere Full Time Posted 1 month ago Product Designer Doist We create tools that promote a calmer, more balanced, more fulfilling way to work and live. Anywhere Full Time Posted 5 days ago MAIN Podcast Community Post a job Remote Work Virtual Wedding Instagram Twitter Login REMOTE JOBS Developer jobs Marketing jobs Product jobs Design jobs Sales jobs Support jobs JOBS IN YOUR CITY Los Angeles jobs New York City jobs San Francisco jobs Chicago jobs Seattle jobs Austin jobs London jobs Paris jobs Berlin jobs POST YOUR JOBS Post a job We\u2019ve helped the world\u2019s top companies hire a talented, diverse pool of job candidates \u2013 view our success stories here. Terms & Privacy Policy & hello@remotewoman.com @ 2020 RemoteWoman \u